---
description: Language stack and style conventions
alwaysApply: true
---
- C is the primary language. Keep it C11, no compiler-specific extensions
  unless a backend genuinely requires them.
- Objective-C is confined to the Metal bridge file(s) only.
- Metal Shading Language kernels live under `metal/`, CUDA kernels under
  `cuda/`.
- No dependency on PyTorch, JAX, or any generic tensor framework in `src/`.
- Favor small, readable functions over generic/abstracted ones — this
  engine targets one model family, not many; don't over-generalize.
